{"title":"How to watch the Tour of Flanders 2025","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-tour-of-flanders","date":1743521234000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-tour-of-flanders\">How to watch the Tour of Flanders 2025</a></p>\n\n<p>The second Monument of the 2025 season takes place on Sunday 6th April with the men’s and women’s Tour of Flanders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Taking place in Belgium, the cobbled Classic pits the riders against a 168km <em>parcours</em> for the women’s race and 268km for the men’s race, taking in the most famous <em><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/best-cobbled-climbs-flanders\">bergs</a> </em>of the Flemish Ardennes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In 2024 the women’s race was won by <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\">Elisa Longo Borghini</a>, who outsprinted Kasia Niewiadoma, and the men’s was won by Mathieu van der Poel, who romped to victory after making a long-range move up the wet cobbles of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/koppenberg-cycling\">Koppenberg</a>. Both will be back to defend their titles this year, with Tadej Pogačar and Wout van Aert spearheading the challenge to Van der Poel, and Lotte Kopecky hoping to take her title back from Longo Borghini.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve got full analysis of the race, teams and starters, a history of its most epic editions and our own experience of riding the (slightly shorter) full course a few years ago in our accompanying detailed <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-flanders-route-riders-sportive-and-all-you-need-to-know\" target=\"_blank\">Tour of Flanders guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Where to watch the Tour of Flanders 2025</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tour-des-Flandres-Cyclist-76-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Xavier Pereyron</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>‘De Ronde’ takes place on Sunday 6th April and you can catch the Tour of Flanders races in the UK on TNT Sports and Discovery+. On TV, the men’s race will be broadcast on TNT Sports 1 from 9am, with the women’s event on air via TNT Sports 2 from 2pm.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the USA and Canada, coverage is on <a href=\"https://www.flobikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Flobikes</a>. In Australia, the Tour of Flanders is available live and on demand on <a href=\"https://www.sbs.com.au/ondemand/sport\" target=\"_blank\">SBS</a>. Throughout Europe, the racing will be broadcast on Eurosport and Discovery+. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If the race isn’t being broadcast in your country or you are travelling abroad, a VPN will allow you to hide your device’s location to access content that is normally geo-blocked. One such VPN provider is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is <a href=\"https://www.techradar.com/reviews/expressvpn\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find free to watch cycling, and costs start from around £5 per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-watch-cycling-for-less-in-the-uk\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling for less in the UK</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Read more:</strong> <strong><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/free-to-air-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">Which countries can watch cycling for free in 2025?</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+4\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-4-1-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Full list of broadcasters</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>TNT Sports: </strong>UK, Ireland</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RTBF &amp; VRT</strong>: Belgium</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RAI</strong>: Italy, San Marino, Vatican City</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>NOS</strong>: Netherlands</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Czech TV</strong>: Czech Republic</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RTVS</strong>: Slovakia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SRG</strong>: Switzerland</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>TV2 Denmark</strong>: Denmark</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>TV2 Norway</strong>: Norway</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>FloBikes</strong>: USA, Canada, Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>ESPN</strong>: Argentina, Bolivia, Chile, Colombia, Ecuador, Paraguay, Peru, Uruguay, Venezuela, Brazil, Belize, Costa Rica, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua, Panama, Mexico, Anguilla, Antigua and Barbuda, Aruba, Bahamas, Barbados, Barbuda, Bermuda, Bonaire, British Virgin Islands, Cayman Islands, Curacao, Dominica, Dominican Republic, Falkland Islands, French Guiana, Grenada, Guadeloupe, Guyana, Haiti, Jamaica, Martinique, Montserrat, Saba, Saint Barthélemy, Saint Eustatius, Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Lucia, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, Suriname, Trinidad and Tobago, Turks and Caicos Islands</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Sky</strong>: New Zealand</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SBS</strong>: Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Supersport</strong>: Angola, Burundi, Benin, Botswana, Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Central African Republic, Chad, Congo, Cape Verde, Ivory Coast, Comoros, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Djibouti, Equatorial Guinea, Eritrea, Ethiopia, Gabon, Gambia, Ghana, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Kenya, Lesotho, Liberia, Madagascar, Malawi, Mauritius, Mayotte, Mozambique, Mali, Mauritania, Namibia, Nigeria, Niger, Réunion, Rwanda, South Africa, Eswatini, Sao Tome and Principe, Saint Helena and Ascension, Senegal, Sierra Leone, Seychelles, Socotra, Tanzania, Togo, Uganda, Zimbabwe, Zambia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Eurosport/Discovery</strong>: Pan-Europe, Asia-Pacific (excluding C